5. Application Specifications (jo me detaje)

a. Architecture

InternLink follows a three-tier architecture consisting of the frontend, backend, and database layers. 
The frontend is built using React, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, providing separate dashboards for students, companies, university staff, and administrators,
all communicating with the backend through REST APIs. The backend, developed using Node.js/Express or Python Flask (depending on final team choice),
handles authentication, authorization, business logic, and data validation. 
The database layer uses MySQL or PostgreSQL to store users, opportunities, applications, and verification statuses, ensuring structured and reliable data management.

b. Database Model

The database is relational, with clearly defined relationships between tables.
The Users table stores all user accounts and roles, while the Opportunities table links each internship post to the company that created it.
The Applications table connects students with the opportunities they apply for, using foreign keys referencing Users and Opportunities. 
The Verification table links university staff decisions to specific opportunities, enabling a verified posting workflow. 
The structure ensures referential integrity and smooth interaction across all system modules.

c. Technologies Used

The frontend uses React, HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create dynamic and reusable UI components. 
The backend is built with Node.js and Express, chosen for its speed, scalability, and efficient REST API handling.
A MySQL or PostgreSQL database is used for secure, structured relational data storage.
Authentication is implemented with JWT for token-based sessions and bcrypt for password hashing.
Git and GitHub support version control, teamwork, and repository management.

d. User Interface Design

The UI provides clean, role-specific dashboards to ensure simplicity and usability.
Students view opportunity cards with filters and an apply option.
Companies have tools to create, edit, and track their listings.
University staff access a list of pending opportunities with direct approve/reject controls.
Administrators see a system-wide dashboard for managing users, verifying listings, and monitoring platform activity.
The design emphasizes clarity, accessibility, and efficiency for all user roles.

e. Security Measures

During registration and throughout system usage, InternLink implements strong security mechanisms.
Passwords are encrypted using bcrypt, and JWT tokens secure user sessions.
Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) ensures users only access authorized features.
All inputs are validated server-side to prevent malicious data.
The system is protected against common attacks such as SQL injection, XSS, and CSRF, and any file uploads undergo safety checks.
On deployment, all communication is secured using HTTPS.
